USER STORY: User Login and Account Access

AS A user,
I WANT TO log into my iSpeak account or toggle to the sign-up form,
SO THAT I can access my saved workout data or create a new account if I do not already have one.

SCENARIO: Successful Login

GIVEN the user opens the iSpeak app and is on the login screen,
WHEN the user enters a valid email and password and selects the "Log In" button,
THEN the system should authenticate the user using Firebase Authentication
WITHIN 3 seconds,
AND redirect the user to their profile dashboard
WITHIN 2 seconds.

SCENARIO: Invalid Login Credentials

GIVEN the user is on the login screen,
WHEN the user enters an incorrect email or password and selects the "Log In" button,
THEN the system should display an error message stating "Invalid email or password"
WITHIN 2 seconds,
AND allow the user to attempt logging in again.

SCENARIO: Missing Login Information

GIVEN the user is on the login screen,
WHEN the user selects the "Log In" button without entering both email and password,
THEN the system should display a message prompting the user to fill in the required fields
WITHIN 1 second.

SCENARIO: Toggle Between Login and Sign Up Forms

GIVEN the user is on the authentication screen,
WHEN the user selects the "Sign Up" tab,
THEN the system should switch the visible form from the login fields to the sign-up fields
WITHIN 1 second,
AND allow the user to enter information to create a new account.
